Ukraine’s Wheat, Barley Yields Increase as Harvesting Begins

-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 
2011-07-01T09:55:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-01/ukraine-s-wheat-barley-yields-increase-as-harvesting-begins.html
Ukraine’s winter barley yields
increased 15 percent from a year earlier and wheat yields are up
22 percent, the  Agriculture Ministry  said.  The winter barley yield rose to an average 2.87 tons a
hectare (2.47 acres) since the harvest began about June 20 from
2.49 tons in the same period last year, the Kiev-based
Agriculture Ministry said in an e-mailed statement yesterday.
Winter wheat yields averaged 3.3 tons a hectare, up from 2.7
tons, over the same period, it said.  Farmers harvested 1 million tons of grain by yesterday,
with 983,000 tons of winter barley.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
